  "text": "The human body contains 2-3 g zinc, most of which is bound to proteins. Over 300 enzymes have been shown to contain zinc, either directly involved in catalysis, as a cofactor, or for structural stabilization [CITATION_1] . Another large group of zinc containing proteins are transcription factors, many of which contain zinc fingers and similar structural motives. From in silico studies searching for known zincbinding patterns, it has been estimated that approximately 10% of the human genome encode for proteins that could bind zinc [CITATION_2] .",
